      • startRecognition

        public void startRecognition(FrameInfo frame)
        The method starts the recognition process for the current image which is set with setImage. The recognition is done in a parallel thread. When the recognition is over, the callback function is called so make sure you implement the RecognitionCallback interface and add the callback object with addRecognitionCallback. WARNING: callback functions WILL be called from background thread so make sure you don't do GUI updates from within callback methods (or use handler to post updates to GUI thread)

      • prepareForNextRecognition

        public void prepareForNextRecognition()
        This method sets the state of the recognizer to READY, if it has been set to DONE (after recognition process). This method should be called from UI thread after handling the result of previous recognition. While state of the Photopay is DONE, no frames are sent to recognition.

      • unlockApplication

        public static boolean unlockApplication(java.lang.String key,
                        android.content.Context context)
                                 throws java.lang.Exception
        Tries to unlock native library with given key for given context. Returns true if application unlock was successful, otherwise returns false. If libPhotoPay.so is not loaded, throws an Exception.
        Parameters:
        key - License key.
        context - Application context
        Returns:
        True on successful unlock, false on unsuccessful unlock.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - When libPhotoPay.so was not loaded.

      • getDraftLibInfo

        public static net.photopay.settings.PPLibInfo getDraftLibInfo()
        returns draft library info - only information which recognizers are built into library. Information about GPU availability and/or information about whether library initialization was successful will not be available. This method does not require library to be initialized.
        Returns:
        Draft information about library or null if libPhotoPay.so was not loaded.
